      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 50,
      "message": "Yes, CPS-2043 will persist new subscription to DB. There is some sample code on the Jira, and it does overlap with this.\n\nWhat you are proposing could be done like so:\n\n    public List<String> getOngoingCmSubscriptions(final DatastoreType datastoreType, \n            final String cmHandleId, final String xpath) {\n        try {\n            final DataNode existingFilterNode = cpsDataService.getDataNodes(...)\n                    .iterator().next();\n            return (List<String>) existingFilterNode.getLeaves().get(\"subscribers\");                   \n        } catch (DataNodeNotFoundException e) {\n            return Collections.emptyList();\n        }\n    }\n\nAlternatively use queryDataNodes() handling empty response instead of try/catch",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-02-08 09:50:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "60f7af36_f0204683",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
