      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 61,
      "message": "This is not correct. Given the cps path query, it can only return 0 or 1 matching DataNodes. This path can only match at most 1 node:\n\n    /datastores/.../filter[@xpath='/xpath1']\n\nThen we want simply return the 'subscribers' leaf-list (though we should convert it to a Set<String>):\n\n    if (existingDataNodes.isEmpty()) {\n        return Collections.emptySet();\n    }\n    final List<String> existingSubscribers = existingNodes.iterator().next().getLeaves().get(\"subscribers\");\n    return new HashSet<String>(existingSubscribers);\n    \nNote I may look at adding queryDataNode variant returning only 1, since we see this pattern '.iterator().next()' all over NCMP codebase.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
